            Error Handling
        </h2>

        <div class="rounded-xl bg-white/5 border border-white/10 p-5">
            <p class="text-gray-400 mb-3">Base64.decode()
will return an error if:</p>
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-300 space-y-2 mb-4">
                <li>The input contains invalid Base64 characters</li>
                <li>The input has incorrect padding</li>
                <li>The decoded bytes are not valid UTF-8</li>
            </ul>
<pre data-filename="Example"><code class="language-soli text-sm"># Invalid Base64 (wrong padding)
try {
    Base64.decode("invalid==")} catch e {
    print("Error: " + e);  # "Error: Invalid Base64: ..."
}

# Valid Base64 with proper error handling
def safe_decode(input: String) -> String
    try {
        return Base64.decode(input)    } catch e {
        print("Failed to decode: " + e)        ""
    }
end</code></pre>
